File: e2e/npm-discovery.e2e.ts, line ~229-232

Current code:
```typescript
// Tool dispatch should fail because no browser extension is connected
// (tab state is 'closed'), but the tool is recognized and dispatched.
const result = await client.callTool('npm-disc-call_echo', {});
expect(result.isError).toBe(true);
// The error message should indicate the tab is not ready, not "unknown tool"
expect(result.content).not.toContain('Unknown tool');
```

The test verifies that the tool IS recognized (not 'Unknown tool') but doesn't verify what the error actually IS. Since no browser extension is connected in this test (it only starts an MCP server, no Chromium), the expected error is that the tab is closed (no matching tab). The error content should contain 'closed' or 'no matching tab'.

Add a positive assertion after the existing negative one:
```typescript
expect(result.content).not.toContain('Unknown tool');
expect(result.content.toLowerCase()).toMatch(/closed|no matching tab/);
```

This ensures the test fails if the tool errors for a completely different reason (e.g., a crash, timeout, or unexpected dispatch error) that happens to not contain 'Unknown tool'.

File: e2e/lifecycle-hooks.e2e.ts

The existing onNavigate test (lines 34-60) tests pushState only:
```typescript
test('onNavigate fires on pushState URL change', async ({ mcpServer, testServer, extensionContext, mcpClient }) => {
  const page = await setupToolTest(mcpServer, testServer, extensionContext, mcpClient);
  await page.evaluate(() => history.pushState({}, '', '/navigated-path'));
  await waitFor(
    async () => {
      const urls = await page.evaluate(() => (globalThis as Record<string, unknown>).__opentabs_onNavigate_urls);
      return Array.isArray(urls) && urls.length > 0;
    },
    10_000, 200, 'onNavigate hook to record URL',
  );
  const urls = await page.evaluate(
    () => (globalThis as Record<string, unknown>).__opentabs_onNavigate_urls as string[],
  );
  expect(urls).toEqual(expect.arrayContaining([expect.stringContaining('/navigated-path')]));
});
```

The SDK documents that onNavigate fires on: pushState, replaceState, popstate, and hashchange. Add two new tests in the same describe block:

**Test 1: hashchange**
```typescript
test('onNavigate fires on hashchange', async ({ mcpServer, testServer, extensionContext, mcpClient }) => {
  const page = await setupToolTest(mcpServer, testServer, extensionContext, mcpClient);

  // Clear any URLs recorded during setup
  await page.evaluate(() => {
    (globalThis as Record<string, unknown>).__opentabs_onNavigate_urls = [];
  });

  // Trigger a hashchange
  await page.evaluate(() => { window.location.hash = '#test-section'; });

  await waitFor(
    async () => {
      const urls = await page.evaluate(() => (globalThis as Record<string, unknown>).__opentabs_onNavigate_urls);
      return Array.isArray(urls) && urls.length > 0;
    },
    10_000, 200, 'onNavigate hook to record hashchange URL',
  );

  const urls = await page.evaluate(
    () => (globalThis as Record<string, unknown>).__opentabs_onNavigate_urls as string[],
  );
  expect(urls).toEqual(expect.arrayContaining([expect.stringContaining('#test-section')]));
});
```

**Test 2: replaceState**
```typescript
test('onNavigate fires on replaceState URL change', async ({ mcpServer, testServer, extensionContext, mcpClient }) => {
  const page = await setupToolTest(mcpServer, testServer, extensionContext, mcpClient);

  await page.evaluate(() => {
    (globalThis as Record<string, unknown>).__opentabs_onNavigate_urls = [];
  });

  await page.evaluate(() => history.replaceState({}, '', '/replaced-path'));

  await waitFor(
    async () => {
      const urls = await page.evaluate(() => (globalThis as Record<string, unknown>).__opentabs_onNavigate_urls);
      return Array.isArray(urls) && urls.length > 0;
    },
    10_000, 200, 'onNavigate hook to record replaceState URL',
  );

  const urls = await page.evaluate(
    () => (globalThis as Record<string, unknown>).__opentabs_onNavigate_urls as string[],
  );
  expect(urls).toEqual(expect.arrayContaining([expect.stringContaining('/replaced-path')]));
});
```

Make sure to import waitFor from './helpers.js' (it should already be imported at line 20).

Note: The e2e-test plugin's adapter IIFE sets up the onNavigate hook to record URLs in globalThis.__opentabs_onNavigate_urls. The pushState test already validates this mechanism works — hashchange and replaceState use the same hook but different browser APIs to trigger the URL change detection.
